{"type":"message","id":"53ac422b","parentId":"b303b0eb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:09:42.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] To restart the OpenClaw Gateway service (or the main OpenClaw agent), use the following command in your terminal:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\nThis will stop and then start the Gateway service, causing it to pick up the active Node.js environment.\n\nIf you want to be sure it uses the correct Node version (like Node 22 with nvm), do the following:\n\n1. Open a terminal window.\n2. Run (if you’re using nvm):\n   ```bash\n   nvm use 22\n   ```\n3. Then run:\n   ```bash\n   openclaw gateway restart\n   ```\n\nThis should make the restarted service use Node 22—the same version that QMD was compiled with.\n\nLet me know if you get any errors or if the QMD backend works after the restart!","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8f547dd0819787fa29c07b2d362a\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":1369,"output":178,"cacheRead":10496,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12043,"cost":{"input":0.002738,"output":0.001424,"cacheRead":0.005248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00941}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774948177745,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8f5277e08197bedfcca2db9a7c40"}}
