{"type":"message","id":"091aa1fa","parentId":"d644f49a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:10:48.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] The QMD backend is still not working—I'm still seeing the same error as before, indicating it's trying to load a native QMD module built for Node 22 under Node 25. So even after the restart, the main process is still running under Node 25 (not Node 22).\n\nSummary:\n- QMD was compiled for Node 22 (NODE_MODULE_VERSION 127)\n- Your current process is using Node 25 (NODE_MODULE_VERSION 141)\n- This mismatch breaks the backend, and restarting didn't change the node environment for the running service\n\nNext step:\nYou need to ensure OpenClaw and QMD are both started under Node 22. This usually means activating Node 22 with nvm in the terminal, then starting/restarting the service from that same terminal/session.\n\nLet me know if you want a step-by-step for this.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8f969668819796a6965e921afcb2\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":1477,"output":180,"cacheRead":11136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12793,"cost":{"input":0.002954,"output":0.0014399999999999999,"cacheRead":0.005568,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009962}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774948245783,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8f95f42081979035dd5ce951c0c7"}}
