{"type":"message","id":"14828fff","parentId":"40ad2b45","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:11:33.920Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here’s a step-by-step guide to make sure OpenClaw (and QMD) run under Node 22:\n\n1. **Open a terminal.**\n\n2. **Switch to Node 22 using nvm:**\n   ```bash\n   nvm use 22\n   ```\n   (If you see an error, try `nvm install 22` first, then repeat the above.)\n\n3. **Restart the OpenClaw Gateway:**\n   ```bash\n   openclaw gateway restart\n   ```\n   or, if you normally start OpenClaw in another way (like `npm start` inside a directory), run that command in this same terminal after the `nvm use 22`.\n\n4. **Confirm the running Node version:**\n   After restarting, you can check the Node version in use by running:\n   ```bash\n   openclaw gateway status\n   ```\n   and/or\n   ```bash\n   ps aux | grep node\n   ```\n   (Look for processes related to OpenClaw and see which node path/version they are using.)\n\n5. **Retest if QMD is working:**  \n   Ask me or your app to check the backend again.\n\nIf at any step you see errors, paste them here and I’ll help troubleshoot. Let me know once you’ve done these steps!","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8fc16f5081979962c4934e65851f\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":181,"output":277,"cacheRead":12672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13130,"cost":{"input":0.00036199999999999996,"output":0.002216,"cacheRead":0.006336,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008914}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774948287333,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb8fc00734819794ad9751a1f131be"}}
