{"type":"message","id":"f656597c","parentId":"812251d5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:24:16.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] QMD is still not working—the same node module version error is present. The backend is still running under Node 25, not Node 22.\n\nThis means the OpenClaw Gateway or the relevant QMD process is still using Node 25, regardless of what you did in your terminal. This often happens if the Gateway is managed by a system service or another supervisor, which may not respect your nvm environment.\n\n**Next things to check:**\n- How did you install/start OpenClaw originally (manual terminal command, systemd, launch agent, etc.)?\n- Are you running the restart command directly in the same shell/session as `nvm use 22`?\n- If OpenClaw starts automatically on boot, it probably uses the system default Node, not your nvm version.\n\nLet me know how you're starting OpenClaw, and I can walk you through making sure it runs under Node 22. If needed, I can help with a systemd/user service config or show you how to force the correct Node version.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb92be3a4c8197bba7d336679d1c38\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":1666,"output":217,"cacheRead":12032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13915,"cost":{"input":0.003332,"output":0.001736,"cacheRead":0.006016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011084}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774949053461,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb92bdab38819782b6d231e896b5ae"}}
