{"type":"message","id":"f07faba5","parentId":"db56ad96","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:50:50.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] QMD is still not working—the error is unchanged. It’s still reporting a native module version mismatch:\n\n- QMD’s native module was built for Node 22 (NODE_MODULE_VERSION 127)\n- The currently running process is using Node 25 (NODE_MODULE_VERSION 141)\n- Or, it’s mixing binaries somehow between node installs/paths\n\nThis means the Node.js version being used to run the service is still not matching what QMD expects, regardless of the `nvm use 22` you did in your shell.\n\n**Next steps:**\n1. Check exactly how OpenClaw is being started (especially if it runs as a background service/daemon or via a script).\n2. The main process needs to be started from a terminal where you’ve run `nvm use 22`—if a system process manager (like systemd, launchctl, a GUI, or a login script) launches it, that often does NOT use your shell’s node version.\n\nIf you show me how you actually launch OpenClaw from scratch, I can help you adjust so it runs under the right Node version and QMD can load. Want to walk through that?","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb98f7a88c8197a4546829483a9997\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":581,"output":245,"cacheRead":13952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14778,"cost":{"input":0.001162,"output":0.00196,"cacheRead":0.0069759999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010098}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774950646660,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cb98f6e14881979694b5bf7040e0e4"}}
