{"type":"message","id":"6d962e3d","parentId":"44dbf7b3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:22:26.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] I tried to add a test entry, but searching for it still returns no results. This suggests that:\n\n- File writes to the memory directory are succeeding at the file-system level\n- But QMD is either not indexing these files, or is still not returning results\n\nThis could mean QMD was not correctly pointed at the right memory path, hasn't indexed/reloaded after the write, or another issue is interfering.\n\nNext steps:\n- Confirm QMD is configured to use the correct memory folder (where memory/qmd-test.md was written)\n- Try forcing a QMD index/reload, if possible\n- Or, run a direct QMD command in your terminal to check its status (if you have a CLI for it)\n\nWant details on any of the above? Let me know how you want to proceed.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cba05f76ac81979e4dac933646f965\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":231,"output":170,"cacheRead":15104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15505,"cost":{"input":0.00046199999999999995,"output":0.0013599999999999999,"cacheRead":0.007552,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009374}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774952542322,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cba05ef7bc81978a141a5b998fa823"}}
