{"type":"message","id":"f693919e","parentId":"6dd2ec2a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:23:56.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] The creation of memory/qmd-test.md means that the assistant (me) can write files to the memory directory—but it does NOT guarantee that the QMD backend is indexing, reading, or serving that memory correctly.\n\n- File write = working file system\n- QMD “working” = able to search/query/read newly added memory through the QMD backend\n\nRight now:\n- The file was written successfully.\n- But when I try to search for the phrase inside (\"QMD Backend Test\"), QMD returns no results or invalid/empty JSON.\n- This suggests the backend is running, but still isn’t indexing or returning memory.\n\nSo, QMD as a memory backend is still not fully functional, even though basic file writing works. There’s likely a config or indexing step missing, or a possible QMD internal error.\n\nWould you like to troubleshoot QMD’s config/path next, or try to force a reload/reindex? Let me know how deep you want to go!","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01725d5fd221b55a0069cba0ba0ab08197b203b69707c446e3\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1","usage":{"input":15580,"output":204,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15784,"cost":{"input":0.03116,"output":0.001632,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032792}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774952632180,"responseId":"resp_01725d5fd221b55a0069cba0b892a48197be7c80739e5cf400"}}
